---
import SiteLayout from "../../../layouts/SiteLayout.astro";
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Law Enforcement | PoliceConduct.org"
  pagePath="/partner/law-enforcement-agency/"
>
  <main class="flex-grow-1">
    <section class="py-vh-3 bg-gray-100 border-bottom border-dark">
      <div class="container">
        <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <ol class="breadcrumb mb-3">
            <li class="breadcrumb-item">
              <a class="link-dark" href="/partner/">Partners</a>
            </li>
            <li class="breadcrumb-item active" aria-current="page">
              Law Enforcement Agency
            </li>
          </ol>
        </nav>
        <div class="row g-4 align-items-end">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-8">
            <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-2">
              Value proposition
            </p>
            <h1 class="display-4 fw-bold">The Resilient Agency Framework</h1>
            <p class="lead text-muted mb-0">
              Leveraging policeconduct.org to lower liability, retain officers,
              and command the narrative.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <div class="text-uppercase small text-muted">Built for</div>
                <div class="fw-semibold">
                  Police Chiefs, Sheriffs, and City Managers
                </div>
                <div class="text-muted small">
                  2026 brings a recruitment crisis, rising premiums, and urgent
                  transparency demands.
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row g-4">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-7">
            <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold">
              1. The 2026 reality: high stakes, low resources
            </h2>
            <div class="d-flex flex-column gap-3 mt-3">
              <div class="border-start border-dark ps-3">
                <h3 class="h6 text-uppercase text-muted mb-1">
                  The settlement surge
                </h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Major cities like New York and Chicago saw record-breaking
                  misconduct payouts in 2025, exceeding $200M in some cases.
                  Mid-sized agencies are seeing take-home car and pursuit
                  settlements cripple their general funds.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="border-start border-dark ps-3">
                <h3 class="h6 text-uppercase text-muted mb-1">
                  The insurance mandate
                </h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Municipal insurers now link premiums to predictive Early
                  Intervention Systems. If you are not tracking data, you are
                  paying more.
                </p>
              </div>
              <div class="border-start border-dark ps-3">
                <h3 class="h6 text-uppercase text-muted mb-1">
                  The paperwork tax
                </h3>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Ninety-nine percent of officers report doing paperwork daily,
                  fueling the 10 to 15 percent vacancy rates seen nationwide.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-5">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-3">
                <div class="text-uppercase small text-muted">
                  Agency survival focus
                </div>
                <ul class="list-unstyled mb-0 d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                  <li class="d-flex align-items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="badge bg-dark rounded-pill">Budget</span>
                    <span>Protect general funds from settlement shocks.</span>
                  </li>
                  <li class="d-flex align-items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="badge bg-dark rounded-pill">People</span>
                    <span>Reduce burnout and keep experienced officers.</span>
                  </li>
                  <li class="d-flex align-items-start gap-2">
                    <span class="badge bg-dark rounded-pill">Trust</span>
                    <span>Tell your story before social media does.</span>
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2 bg-light border-top border-bottom border-dark">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">
          2. Our solution: the unified integrity suite
        </h2>
        <p class="text-muted">
          policeconduct.org modernizes Internal Affairs and risk management into
          a single CJIS-compliant platform.
        </p>
        <div class="row g-4 mt-2">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-1">
                  A. Defensive data
                </p>
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">Liability mitigation</h3>
                <ul class="list-unstyled mb-0 d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                  <li>
                    Audit-ready IA with an immutable database for complaints and
                    investigations.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Insurance benchmarking analytics that prove low-risk
                    performance.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-1">
                  B. First-sign early intervention
                </p>
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">Officer wellness</h3>
                <ul class="list-unstyled mb-0 d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                  <li>
                    Burnout detection flags stress patterns before incidents
                    escalate.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Positive recognition highlights high
                    commendation-to-complaint ratios.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-4">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark h-100">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                <p class="text-uppercase small text-muted mb-1">
                  C. The transparency portal
                </p>
                <h3 class="h6 fw-semibold">Narrative control</h3>
                <ul class="list-unstyled mb-0 d-flex flex-column gap-2">
                  <li>
                    Public-facing dashboards show trends without exposing
                    sensitive data.
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    Debunking tools counter viral misinformation with verified
                    metadata.
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2">
      <div class="container">
        <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold mb-3">
          3. Strategic ROI for the chiefâ€™s office
        </h2>
        <div class="table-responsive">
          <table class="table table-bordered align-middle">
            <thead class="table-light">
              <tr>
                <th scope="col">Priority</th>
                <th scope="col">The old way (2024)</th>
                <th scope="col">The policeconduct.org way (2026)</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Budget control</strong></td>
                <td>Settlement costs are a black hole.</td>
                <td
                  ><strong>30% reduction</strong> in preventable litigation via early
                  intervention.</td
                >
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Recruitment</strong></td>
                <td>Officers leave due to toxic IA cultures.</td>
                <td
                  ><strong>Fair, transparent IA</strong> that rewards excellence and
                  supports wellness.</td
                >
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Staffing</strong></td>
                <td>IA sergeants spend 60% of time on data entry.</td>
                <td
                  ><strong>Automated workflows</strong> free supervisors for field
                  training.</td
                >
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td><strong>Public trust</strong></td>
                <td>No comment during investigations.</td>
                <td
                  ><strong>Proactive data sharing</strong> builds community capital
                  before crises.</td
                >
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="py-vh-2 bg-gray-100 border-top border-dark">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="row g-4 align-items-center">
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-7">
            <h2 class="h4 fw-semibold">4. Why policeconduct.org?</h2>
            <ul class="list-unstyled mb-0 d-flex flex-column gap-2">
              <li>
                <strong>Zero-lift integration:</strong> Plug into existing CAD/RMS
                systems.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Built for 2026 law:</strong> Auto-map CA SB 2, TX MIR, and
                state mandates.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong>Officer-first design:</strong> Built to support fairness and
                wellness.
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="col-12 col-lg-5">
            <div class="card shadow-sm rounded-0 border-dark">
              <div class="card-body d-flex flex-column gap-3">
                <div class="text-uppercase small text-muted">
                  Suggested next step
                </div>
                <p class="mb-0">
                  Want a briefing memo for a City Council or Oversight Board
                  that compares platform cost against average misconduct
                  settlements?
                </p>
                <a
                  class="btn btn-dark rounded-0"
                  href="/about/contact?whoami=Partner&message=I%27m%20interested%20in%20a%20Resilient%20Agency%20Framework%20briefing%20memo%20for%20my%20city."
                >
                  Request the briefing memo
                </a>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</SiteLayout>
